cisc187.util

Class ArrayQueue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • cisc187.util.ArrayQueue<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Queue<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>

    public class ArrayQueue<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Queue<E>
    Implements a generic queue of fixed size using a raw array as a backing store. Elements are stored in array indices 0 .. n-1.
    Author:
    dparillo@sdccd.edu

      • enqueue

        public void enqueue(E element)
             throws FullQueueException
        Adds the specified element to the tail of this Queue.
        PRECONDITION: the Queue's size is less than its capacity.
        POSTCONDITION: the element is now the tail element in this Queue, none of the other elements have been changed, and the size is increased by 1.
        Specified by:
        enqueue in interface Queue<E>
        Parameters:
        element - the element to add to the queue
        Throws:
        FullQueueException - if the Queue is at capacity.

      • dequeue

        public E dequeue()
        Removes the element at the head of this Queue. Returns the element removed, or null if there was no such element.
        PRECONDITION: the Queue's size is greater than zero.
        POSTCONDITION: the head element in this Queue has been removed, none of the other elements have been changed, and the size is decreased by 1.
        Specified by:
        dequeue in interface Queue<E>
        Returns:
        the element removed, or null if the queue is empty.
